The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, April 05, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, April 5, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Mir Bahar Ghat (Raja Katra) will be blocked from 5 am to midnight by devotees for Hanuman Jayanti.				 																																	A Hanuman Jayanti procession will cross the Hooghly via Howrah bridge at 6 am. It will travel down Kalakar Street, BK Pal Avenue and proceed to the Dum Dum mandir.				 																School talk				 																																	A panel discussion and interactive session on Do schools need to change?, hosted by Calcutta Chamber of Commerce and Vikramshila Education Resource Society, at the Chamber, 5 pm.				 																Dance				 																																	Thai classical dances, organised by Royal Thai Embassy and Royal Thai consulate-general, at Madhusudan Mancha, 7 pm.				 																Theatre				 																																	Virus-M, a Ganakrishti production directed by Bratya Basu, to be staged at Academy of Fine Arts, at 6.30 pm.				 																Workshop				 																																	A workshop on boat-making, painting and drawing will be conducted by Scottish sculptor-painter Kenny Munro to mark the 150th birth anniversary of Sir Patrick Geddes at School of Art and Craft, in Asghar Mistri Lane, 8 am to 11 am and 6 pm to 8 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition-cum-sale of over 250 Indian paintings and sculptures at Idiyas Gallery on Dover Lane, 10.30 am to 7.30 pm. 				 																																	Water colours by Sambhu Das are on view at Academy of Fine Arts, from 3 pm to 8 pm.
